</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="18A20733CC792E300FE8535058BAA3CE" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" type="notes">
<paragraph id="6AB2F50678F2CC1C5664D2D1BD42FDB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7CF8C5BB44904A5C99A433E9C6C4CEF2" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">
<taxonomicName id="FB7FA3A651E0239D991B38120A92EF4C" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Commelina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Commelina benghalensis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="benghalensis">
<emphasis id="046E14EDB0E5EF01E681F7124605C465" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">Commelina benghalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a weed from the Old World subtropics. In the Canary Islands, it is only known from Gran Canaria (
<bibRefCitation id="234B4DE83A9798BFF1198E5AB5541989" author="Acebes Ginoves, J R" journalOrPublisher="Gobierno de Canarias, La Laguna" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" refId="B6456181" refString="Acebes Ginoves, J R, Leon Arencibia, M C, Rodriguez Navarro, M L, 2010. Lista de especies silvestres de Canarias. Hongos, plantas y animales terrestres. Gobierno de Canarias, La Laguna" title="Lista de especies silvestres de Canarias. Hongos, plantas y animales terrestres." year="2010">
Acebes 
<normalizedToken id="9835414B09C6EAEF488840F236BCFE8C" originalValue="GinovÃ©s">Ginoves</normalizedToken>
et al. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
), although most (if not all) records probably date back to the 19th century (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="CD9794A24C0B31E8B71E8F6C6ACFE9F9" author="Buch, CL" journalOrPublisher="Archives de Botanique" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" pagination="481 - 508" refId="B6508930" refString="Buch, CL, 1833. Catalogue des Plantes spontanees qui ont ete jusqu'ici trouvees dans les iles Canaries. Archives de Botanique 1: 481 - 508" title="Catalogue des Plantes spontanees qui ont ete jusqu'ici trouvees dans les iles Canaries" volume="1" year="1833">Buch 1833</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CDE93B5460E892C1E3579AACC172170B" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">Since 2015, it has been known from a single locality in Tenerife. In Palm-Mar, it persists on the wall of a manhole. Its presence was regularly confirmed since then.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14EEE8E30B140C3F9D543BD888DBED16" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">
This species differs from the common and invasive 
<taxonomicName id="0AFF17C9CB2722ABE5B14E4185FFD5C7" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Commelina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Commelina" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="59CEC50349F34D58BF31ECDAF188A135" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">Commelina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the Canary Islands (
<taxonomicName id="EC7F577323193DF22DC8FC5AF2F81A3F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. diffusa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="diffusa">
<emphasis id="E8715FE4C89BBBE4646503F73FACB763" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">C. diffusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the spathe margins that are fused near base. This characteristic is shared with 
<taxonomicName id="224AA11B9504156A3A6E4C603843255F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. latifolia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="62AD9DA9F78C112A2E277045DD337F46" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">C. latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hochst. ex A. Rich., an African species that recently naturalised in La Palma (
<bibRefCitation id="9B79E591C55A53E6FD4141C9858F7C17" author="Otto, R" journalOrPublisher="Collectanea Botanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" refId="B6509388" refString="Otto, R, Verloove, F, 2016. New xenophytes from La Palma (Canary Islands, Spain), with emphasis on naturalized and (potentially) invasive species. Collectanea Botanica 35" title="New xenophytes from La Palma (Canary Islands, Spain), with emphasis on naturalized and (potentially) invasive species" volume="35" year="2016">Otto and Verloove 2016</bibRefCitation>
). It can be distinguished from the latter by the typical pubescence that consists of reddish hairs and all petals, including the minute lower one, being blue.
</paragraph>
